<bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>History</head>

	<p><corpname>Ives and Pierce</corpname>, a rural business in <geogname>Canaan, Connecticut</geogname>, was owned by <persname>Henry B. Ives</persname> and <persname>Robert D. Pierce</persname>, and sold grain, chicken feed, poultry, and agricultural supplies to local farmers. The business also sold coal to local residents. </p>

</bioghist>


<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>The collection contains the financial and business records of Ives and Pierce.</p>
</scopecontent>
<arrangement encodinganalog="351$b" id="a5">
	<head>Arrangement</head>
	<p></p>
<p><emph render="bold">Series I: Journals and Daybooks </emph> (<date>1895-1929</date>) consists of thirty journals 
and four daybooks which list daily sales made at the store.  The entries include the transaction date, the customer's name, a description of the item sold, and the purchase price.</p>
<p><emph render="bold">Series II: Coal and Account Books </emph> (<date>1900-1928</date>) consists of two volumes.  The first 
volume lists sales of coal for 1922 to 1928. The second volume is an account book, 1900-1925, which records coal and grain 
purchased.</p>
</arrangement>
<relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
	<head>Related Material</head>
